step 1 :- enable raspberry pi camera by using raspberry pi software congiguration tool
pi@raspberrypi:-$ sudo raspi.config
 
step 2 :- select interfacing options -> camera -> enable
 
step 3 :- after this reboot the system, using sudo reboot command
pi@raspberrypi:-$sudo reboot
 
step 4 :- create a folder which is used to store pictures captured by Pi Camera.
 
step 5 :- Write a Python Script to capture images and save them in folder.
 
step 6 :- install pi-camera packages.
sudo apt-get install python-picamera
sudo apt-get install python3-picamera
sudo pip install picamera
 
